(Atho Network Stack) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Date: 2026-04-04) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This document explains the current stack, why each layer exists, and where the implementation) Tj
T*
(lives.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Design Goal) Tj
T*
(Atho keeps Python as the controller while moving performance-critical execution into native code) Tj
T*
(where practical. The result is maintainability + speed:) Tj
T*
(- Python owns orchestration, APIs, configuration, and UI.) Tj
T*
(- C/C++ binaries own heavy loops and cryptographic hot paths.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Layer 0: Binary Runtime and Hash Pinning) Tj
T*
(Purpose: load native components safely and consistently across OS/arch.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key behavior:) Tj
T*
(- Canonical binary location: Binaries/<platform-tag>/.) Tj
T*
(- Every built binary is registered with SHA3-384 hash in:) Tj
T*
(- Binaries/pin_registry.json) Tj
T*
(- Binaries/<platform-tag>/binary_meta.json) Tj
T*
(- Strict load mode via ATHO_BINARIES_STRICT=1 prevents fallback to legacy paths.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Code paths:) Tj
T*
(- Src/Utility/oscompat.py) Tj
T*
(- Src/Utility/binarypin.py) Tj
T*
(- Src/Falcon/Falcon/install_platform_binary.py) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why: runtime integrity, reproducible deployments, and safer upgrades.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Layer 1: Cryptography) Tj
T*
(Purpose: deterministic post-quantum signing and verification with pinned binaries.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Components:) Tj
T*
(- falcon_cli binary for keygen/sign/verify.) Tj
T*
(- Optional FFI verify library \(libatho_falcon_verify\) for in-process verification acceleration.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Code paths:) Tj
T*
(- Src/Accounts/falconcli.py) Tj
T*
(- Src/Falcon/Falcon/build_falcon_verify_shared.sh) Tj
T*
(- Src/Utility/const.py \(pin policy and verifier settings\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why: keep Falcon verification fast while preserving strict binary trust policy.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Layer 2: Transaction Wire and Integer Accounting) Tj
T*
(Purpose: compact tx transport and exact accounting.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Current behavior:) Tj
T*
(- Transport codec is compact binary \(ATX2; ATX1 decode compatibility\).) Tj
T*
(- Inputs/outputs are encoded using varints and fixed-size digests where appropriate.) Tj
T*
(- Witness is encoded as raw bytes internally.) Tj
T*
(- API/UI display remains stable \(human-readable fields, canonical encoding\), while internal math) Tj
T*
ET
